          "body": "Peter's *we have left everything* (19:27) is the chapter's most honest sentence — and Jesus does not rebuke it. He answers it. In *the regeneration* (*palingenesia*, 19:28), the Twelve will sit on twelve thrones judging the twelve tribes of Israel. The promise expands beyond the apostles in verse 29: *everyone* who has left houses or family or farms *for My name's sake* receives a hundredfold and inherits eternal life. The exchange rate is asymmetric in the disciple's favor. The chapter closes with the reversal saying (19:30 — first will be last, last first), which becomes the opening and closing of chapter 20's parable of the workers (20:1-16). The kingdom's reward economy is real, but its ranking system will surprise everyone — including its early adopters."
